title: "Multi-Wing GPT Autonomy Architecture"
version: "0.2.0-candidate"
date-released: "2026-05-31"

type: software
license: MIT

authors:
  - name: "SamuraiWriter7"

repository-code: "https://github.com/SamuraiWriter7/multi-wing-gpt-autonomy-architecture"

abstract: >
  Multi-Wing GPT Autonomy Architecture is a conceptual and architectural
  specification for governed structural autonomy in role-based GPT and
  agentic AI systems. It defines a staged autonomy model, multi-wing role
  distribution, safety layers, governance boundaries, action permission
  categories, conformance levels, use cases, alignment mapping, and a
  standardization-oriented Working Draft 0 for systems that require role
  consistency, reviewability, accountability, traceability, and human
  authority preservation.

